<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="81">Distribution.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="81">
<collectingCountry name="Japan">Japan</collectingCountry>
, Honshu (Akika Pref., 
<collectingRegion country="Japan" name="Shizuoka">Shizuoka Pref.</collectingRegion>
); Ryukyu Islands (Amami-o-shima).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="81" type="ecology">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="81">Ecology.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="81">
Growing in open rich marshy meadows, along stream margins and in sandy terrain amongst low scrub, sea level to 
<quantity metricMagnitude="3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.3" unit="m" value="1300.0">1300 m</quantity>
of elevation. Flowering in July and August. Germination epigeal.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
